solutions.content:
For a given element at position `i`, it's shortest distance to the `C` is `min(shortest_distance_to_left_occuence[i], shortest_distance_to_right_occurence[i])`, where `shortest_distance_to_left_occurence[i] = 0 if S[i] == C else shortest_distance_to_left_occurence[i-1] + 1`. Similarly `shortest_distance_to_right_occurence[i] = 0 if S[i] == C else shortest_distance_to_left_occurence[i+1] + 1`.

First pass keeps track of the shortest distance to the left occurence of the `C` and second pass takes into account right occurences of `C`.
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> shortestToChar(string S, char C) {
        vector<int> distance(S.size(), S.size());
        for (int i = 0; i < S.size(); ++i) {
            if (S[i] == C) {
                distance[i] = 0;
            } else if (i > 0) {
                distance[i] = distance[i-1] + 1;
            }
        }
        for (int i = S.size() - 2; i >= 0; --i) {
            distance[i] = min(distance[i], distance[i+1] + 1);
        }
        return distance;
    }
};
```

