# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->Using two pointer approach.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->We will have two pointers, and change them over when the right one will be more closer, the right one will become left pointer , and we'll get a  new right pointer if there exists one.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(N) {for solution array only}
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution
{
    public int[] shortestToChar(String s, char c)
    {
        char[] arr=s.toCharArray();
        boolean f2=false; //flag for telling if there is second right available
        int ptr1=0,ptr2=0;
        for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++) //gets the first occurence
            if(c==arr[i])
            {
                ptr1=i;
                break;
            }

        for(int i=ptr1+1;i<arr.length;i++) //gets the second occurence if there is one , thats why the flag is used which is false by default
            if(c==arr[i])
            {
                ptr2=i;
                f2=true;
                break;
            }

        int[] result=new int[s.length()];
        for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++)
        {
            if(f2) //if second occurence exists
            {
                if((Math.abs(ptr1-i)>=(Math.abs(ptr2-i)))) //gets triggered if the right one is more closer or equally closer
                { //inside we are changing the pointers
                    int j;
                    boolean flag=false; //tells if we have another occurence of given character
                    for(j=ptr2+1;j<arr.length;j++)
                        if(arr[j]==c)
                        {
                            flag=true;
                            break;
                        }
                    if(flag) //updates both pointers if we get an occurence
                    {
                        ptr1=ptr2;
                        ptr2=j;
                    }
                    else //else only ptr1 will be changed , and this this if will not be triggered again
                    {
                        ptr1=ptr2;
                        f2=false;
                    }
                }
            }
            result[i]=Math.abs(ptr1-i);
        }
        return result
        ;
    }
}
```

