**2 Pointers**

Record all indexes of `c`, then determine the **NEAREST distance from BOTH SIDES** for each `s[i]`.
> Note: for BOUNDARY condition, I add `-Infinity` and `Infinity` at both ends.

```
s=loveleetcode, c="e"
ind=[-Infinity,3,5,6,11,Infinity]

s[0]~[3]:  compare i with left=-Infinity, right=3
s[4]~[5]:  compare i with left=3, right=5
s[6]:      compare i with left=5, right=6
s[7]~[11]: compare i with left=6, right=11
```

```
var shortestToChar = function(s, c) {
    let ind=[-Infinity];
    for(let i=0; i<s.length; i++){
        if(s[i]==c){ind.push(i)};
    }
    ind.push(Infinity);

    let now=0, output=[];
    for(let j=0; j<s.length; j++){
        if(j>ind[now]){now++};
		// now-1=LEFT pointer, now=RIGHT pointer
        output.push(Math.min(Math.abs(j-ind[now-1]), Math.abs(j-ind[now])));
    }
    return output;
};
```

**2 Pass**

Loop from left to get **NEAREST distance from LEFT**.
Then loop from right again, update the **MINIMUM of two**.
```
s=loveleetcode, c="e"
            l o v e l e e t c o d e
from left   X X X 0 1 0 0 1 2 3 4 0
from right  3 2 1 0 1 0 0 4 3 2 1 0
MIN         3 2 1 0 1 0 0 1 2 2 1 0
```

```
var shortestToChar = function(s, c) {
    let output=[], dis=Infinity;
    for(let i=0; i<s.length; i++){
        dis=s[i]==c? 0: ++dis;
        output.push(dis);
    }
    dis=Infinity;
    for(let j=s.length-1; j>=0; j--){
        dis=s[j]==c? 0: ++dis;
		// compare MIN of dis(left) & dis(right)
        output[j]=Math.min(dis, output[j]);
    }
    return output;
};
```

