**Explanation** - We first create a TreeSet containing the positions of character c in string s. Then we iterate through all the indices of string s and find the nearest two values from the current position in the string using this set. One of these two values is less than the current position and the other greater. We calculate the difference of both from the current position. The lower one is the answer. We do this for all positions in the string.
```
class Solution {
    public int[] shortestToChar(String s, char c) {
        var posSet = IntStream.range(0,s.length()).filter(i -> s.charAt(i) == c)
            .collect(TreeSet<Integer>::new,TreeSet::add,TreeSet::addAll);

        return IntStream.range(0,s.length()).map(i -> {
            var floor = Objects.requireNonNullElse(posSet.floor(i), Integer.MAX_VALUE);
            var ceil  = Objects.requireNonNullElse(posSet.ceiling(i), Integer.MAX_VALUE);
            return Integer.min(Math.abs(floor - i), Math.abs(ceil - i));
        }).toArray();
    }
}
```

