**Approach**:  As we have to reverse the substring beween every pair, so we store the index whenever we get an open parenthesis and since it is given that it is balanced means if we encounter any closed parenthesis then the we must have a index of its matching open '(' parenthesis at the tos. we pop it and reverse from the index at tos and 
the current index we are on and the process repeats.

**Time** : O(n^2) **space** : O(n)

```
class Solution {
public:
    string reverseParentheses(string s) {

        stack<int>st;
        for(int i=0;i<s.size();i++){

            if(s[i]=='(') st.push(i);
            else if(s[i]==')'){
                int j=st.top();
                st.pop();
                s[i]='$',s[j]='$';
                reverse(s.begin()+j+1,s.begin()+i);
            }
        }
        string res="";
        for(auto x:s){
            if(x!='$') res+=x;
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

