1. Create a Stack to store characters that are not within parentheses.
2. Iterate through each character in the input string s.
3. If the current character is a closing parentheses, pop all the characters from the Stack until the matching opening parentheses is found. Append the popped characters to a new StringBuilder in reverse order.
4. If the current character is not a parentheses, push it onto the Stack.
5. After iterating through all the characters in s, pop all the remaining characters from the Stack and append them to the end of the result StringBuilder.
6. Return the result StringBuilder in reverse order.
```
public String reverseParentheses(String s) {
   Stack<Character> stack = new Stack<>();
   // Iterate through each character in the string
   for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
       // If the character is a closing parentheses, reverse the string within the parentheses
       if (c == ')') {
           StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
           // Pop characters from the stack until an opening parentheses is found
           while (!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() != '(') {
               sb.append(stack.pop());
           }
           // Pop the opening parentheses
           stack.pop();
           // Add the reversed string within parentheses back to the stack
           while (!sb.isEmpty()) {
               stack.add(sb.charAt(0));
               sb.deleteCharAt(0);
           }
       }
       // If the character is not a closing parentheses, add it to the stack
       else {
           stack.add(c);
       }
   }
   // Create a StringBuilder to store the final output
   StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder();
   // Pop all the characters from the stack and add them to the StringBuilder
   while (!stack.isEmpty()) {
       ans.append(stack.pop());
   } 
   // Reverse the StringBuilder and convert it to a String
   return ans.reverse().toString();
}
```
