## Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Since it is given that the parantheses are balanced, it is only required to know the where each valid parantheses' pair exists. Use a stack to keep track of this, similar to problems where the task is to determine whether the given string is a valid parantheses arrangement or not.

Maintain a stack```s```of integers that stores the indices of all```(```characters. Iterate through the input string```t```. Let the iterator be```i```.
If```t[i]=='('```push ```i```to the stack. If```t[i]==')'```reverse the string from the index```s.top()```to the index```i```.
Finally, copy all alphabet characters to a new output string and return the so-obtained string.

## Complexity
- Time complexity
    - Given the length of the input string is *n*: *O(n)*
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
