1. Count the frequency of all the letters.
2. Go through all the frequencies, and add them to a set.  If a number already exists in a set, it will return false if you try to add it.  If it does return false decrease its frequency, and try and add it again.  Repeat this until it gets added, and then move on to the next number.
3. Everytime you remove an item increase the count.

