# Intuition
- Given a string. We have to check whether it is good or not.
- It is good iff every character's freqency in the string is dfferent.
- We need to determine minimum number of deletions need to do so as to make the string good.
- Intuition is to keep a track of frequency of all previous characters that we have kept in our string. We can do this using set.

# Approach
- We are using a unordered_map to store the frequency of different characters in the string.
- Then we will iterate over the map and check if current frequency exists in map or not. If it exists then we decrement the current frequency and again check.
- We will continue this untill either the freqency becomes unique or zero.
- Once the frequency of character becomes unique, we will be adding that in our set
Then we move to next character. 
- We continue this for all characters.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)

- Space complexity:
O(N)
# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minDeletions(string s) {
        unordered_map<char, int> m;
        for(auto i : s){
            m[i]++;
        }
        unordered_set<int> st;
        int ans = 0;
        for(auto i : m){
            int temp = i.second;
            while(temp > 0 && st.find(temp) != st.end()){
                temp--;
                ans++;
            }
            if(temp != 0){
                st.insert(temp);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```
