solutions.content:
**Approach:**
* Store the frequencies of each character in the string.
* Sort the frequency array in ascending order.
* Store the maximum frequency of character i.e. keep=f[25].
* Store the previous frequency i.e. prev=keep.
* Iterate through the frequency array from f[24]....f[0].
* for each element from 24 to 0, store the minimum out of prev frquency-1 and f[i] in prev.
* and add prev to keep.(P.s: keep variable is for no of elements we are choosing to keep)
* return the total no of characters in string - keep. 
```
class Solution 
{
    public int minDeletions(String s) 
    {
        int freq[] = new int[26];
        for (char c : s.toCharArray())
            freq[c - 'a']++;
        Arrays.sort(freq);
        int keep = freq[25], prev = keep;
        for (int i = 24; i >= 0 && freq[i] != 0 && prev != 0; i--) 
        {
            prev = Math.min(freq[i], prev - 1);
            keep += prev;
        }
        return s.length() - keep;
    }
}
```

