# Intuition
Intuition is simple greedy based, If any 2 frequency is same then we will reduce this frequency to it's closest frequency which have value 0.


# Approach
we will take an array v of size n, where index i is the frequency. we will store count of frequency in v.

To keep track of closest frequency in which other greater frequency can be reduced, we will store all these elements in set.

now we will run a loop and if v[i]>1, then we will find lower_bound of i say it. then decrese it-- and ans will be abs(*it-i).

Edge case:- if lower_bound is the first element of set. It means there is no smaller index left so we have to delete all the elements and if v[i]==0. then again put it in set.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$ O(n *(Log(n))) $$



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minDeletions(string s) {
        map<char,int>mp;
        for(auto i:s){
            mp[i]+=1;
        }
        int n=s.size();
        vector<int> v(n+1,0);

        for(auto i:mp){
            v[i.second]++;
        }

        set<int> st;
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i+=1){
            if(v[i]==0){
                st.insert(i);
            }
        }

        int i=1,ans=0;
        while(i<n){
            if(v[i]>1){
                auto it=st.lower_bound(i);

                // if all the minimum index is already filled then we have to delete all the elements
                if(it==st.begin()){
                    ans+=i;
                    v[i]-=1;
                    if(v[i]==0)st.insert(i);
                    continue;
                }

                // nearest index of i(ind<i) which is not filled
                it--;
                int ind= *it;
                int val= abs(ind-i);
                v[i]-=1;
                ans+=val;
                st.erase(ind);
            }else{
                i+=1;
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
```
